# Nested While Loop Assignment
# Purpose:
# This program demonstrates the use of nested while loops.
# The outer while loop controls the number of rows,
# and the inner while loop prints numbers from 1 up to the current row.

# Get the number of rows from the user
rows = int(input("Enter the number of rows: "))

i = 1  # Outer loop variable

while i <= rows:
    j = 1  # Inner loop variable

    while j <= i:
        print(j, end=" ")
        j += 1

    print()  # Move to the next line
    i += 1
